The European Union is changing the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the centres of Service for Visa Applicants before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011 the processing of visas at the US Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will be present at the Service Centres for Visa Applicants (CSA, according to its initials in French) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The staff of CSA will take biometric information from the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will present some advantages for candidates, among which it mentions the following:
The total cost to treat the visa will be lower, it will not be necessary to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for the treatment of visa and another for the mail service delivers the document.
The aspiring will realize a one-time payment that will cover the three services.
The current tariff will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, 150 dollars in the case with visa (ci- includes visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for the visas of traders and investors.
Those wishing to renew their visas will not be present at an interview with the Consular Representative, they will be available only to the nearest CSA where they will present documents and they will take their fingerprints.
Because of the fact that biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section stay less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to the Consulates in Ciudad Juàrez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service tariff of 26 dollars.
